    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is MRI breast with contrast painful?",
        "answer": "No. You may feel a cool sensation when the dye is injected, but the scan itself is painless.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How soon will I get results?",
        "answer": "Most patients receive their report the next working day.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I breastfeed after contrast?",
        "answer": "Yes. Current guidelines say breastfeeding can continue normally; less than 0.04 % of gadolinium reaches breast milk.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What if a lesion is found?",
        "answer": "Your doctor may recommend additional imaging, MRI-guided biopsy, or short-interval follow-up. Cadabams Diagnostics performs on-site biopsies for faster answers.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is it covered by insurance?",
        "answer": "Most policies cover medically-indicated MRI Breast with Contrast; our front-desk team assists with pre-authorisation.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What happens if an abnormality is found on my MRI Breast with Contrast?",
        "answer": "Your doctor will discuss findings. The report includes a BI-RADS assessment. Recommendations include follow-up or biopsy, based on the category."
      }
    ],
